Trilby Clark https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trilby_Clark 0 Trilby Clark (30 August 1896 – 7 July 1983) was an Australian actress who appeared in British films beginning in the silent film era. She was a leading lady in British films during the 1920s and early 1930s. Trilby Clark was born in Adelaide, Australia as Gwendolyn Gladys Blakely Clark. She died in London in 1983.
